MicroLink Creator is a modern and efficient URL shortener application built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. This project allows users to convert long URLs into short, shareable links with ease. It also supports redirection from the shortened URL back to the original URL.

Features:
Shorten Long URLs: Quickly generate compact and shareable links.
Custom Short Codes: Each URL is assigned a unique short code.
Redirection: Automatically redirect users from the short link to the original URL.
Responsive Design: A visually appealing and user-friendly interface.
Database Integration: Stores URLs and their short codes in MongoDB.

Technologies Used:
Node.js: Backend runtime environment.
Express.js: Web framework for building the application.
MongoDB: Database for storing URLs and short codes.
EJS: Template engine for rendering dynamic HTML.
ShortID: Library for generating unique short codes.


